      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\n### pricing.py\ndef calculate_user_discount(price, user_status):\n    if price < 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"Price cannot be negative\")\n    if user_status == \"premium\":\n        return price * 0.8\n    elif user_status == \"gold\":\n        return price * 0.9\n    else:\n        return price\n```\n\n```python\n### test_pricing.py\ndef test_negative_price_edge_case(self):\n    with self.assertRaises(ValueError):\n        calculate_user_discount(-50, \"premium\")\n```\n\nBy raising a `ValueError` when the price is negative, we ensure that the test will fail with a meaningful error message instead of returning an incorrect result. The test now checks that the function correctly raises an exception when given a negative price.",
